The paper discusses the Orthogonal Matching Pursuit (OMP) algorithm for sparse recovery, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on the restricted isometry property (RIP) and online recovery guarantees suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include Machine Learning (cs.LG), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
